lor=#5a3f10;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="1455" y="-0" width="301" height="140" as="geometry"/></mxCell></object><object label="Future humans count&lt;br&gt;(discounted)&lt;br&gt;[1+2+4+5]&lt;br&gt;→ The Humane League&lt;br&gt;   24 lives-eq/$1k · 98% best&lt;br&gt;   runner-up Clean Air Task Force · 2%&lt;br&gt;▼ 19 more worldviews" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + climate_tipping_points + future_humans_matter_with_discounting&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Future people are inside the circle, but with a positive pure-time discount rate — the moderate longtermist position. A modest discount is enough to keep present, measurable global health competitive with future-protecting work; remove it (the next assumption) and the astronomical numbers take over. || Chain: 0 parochial → 1 far_away_humans → 2 animals_somewhat → 4 climate_tipping_points → 5 future_humans_matter_with_discounting" link="https://viewer.diagrams.net/?lightbox=1&amp;nav=1&amp;chrome=0#Uhttps%3A%2F%2Fraw.githubusercontent.com%2Fmorganrivers%2Ftrain_to_crazy_town%2Fmain%2Fdiagram%2Ftrain_tree__w1_2_4_5.drawio" id="w1_2_4_5"><mxCell style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontSize=11;fillColor=#f5d3b8;strokeColor=#cc7a33;fontColor=#5a300e;dashed=1;dashPattern=8 4;strokeWidth=3;fontStyle=1;" vertex="1" parent="1"><mxGeometry x="1249" y="271" width="301" height="140" as="geometry"/></mxCell></object><object label="Animals matter a lot&lt;br&gt;(RP welfare ranges)&lt;br&gt;[1+2+4+7]&lt;br&gt;→ Shrimp Welfare Project&lt;br&gt;   21k lives-eq/$1k · 72% best&lt;br&gt;   runner-up Wild insects (humane pesticides) · 28%&lt;br&gt;(Bob Fischer, Brian Tomasik)" tooltip="&lt;b&gt;parochial + far_away_humans + animals_somewhat + climate_tipping_points + animals_matter_a_lot&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Replace the neuron-count proxy with Rethink Priorities&#x27; welfare-range estimates (Fischer et al.) and count invertebrates — shrimp, insects, and the ~10^19 soil animals. U